"title": "1424: predictions",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1424: predictions",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Speaking authoritatively of the future. Since God knows the future he is able to reveal it to people beforehand. Predictions, which are often but not necessarily contained in prophecies, should not be confused with promises or expressions of intention.</p>\n<h2>God's knowledge of the future</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:15-Gen41:16\">GEN 41:15–41:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:28\">GEN 41:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:17\">GEN 18:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num24:2-Num24:4\">NUM 24:2–24:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:24-Isa44:26\">ISA 44:24–44:26</a></p>\n<h2>Impossible to predict the future apart from God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl8:7\">ECC 8:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl7:14\">ECC 7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:22-Isa41:24\">ISA 41:22–41:24</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ predicted the future</h2>\n<h3>Concerning his death and resurrection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:21\">MAT 16:21</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:31\">MRK 8:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:22\">LUK 9:22</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:22-Matt17:23\">MAT 17:22–17:23</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:31\">MRK 9:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:44\">LUK 9:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:18-Matt20:19\">MAT 20:18–20:19</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:33-Mark10:34\">MRK 10:33–10:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:31-Luke18:33\">LUK 18:31–18:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:19-John2:21\">JHN 2:19–2:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:32-John12:33\">JHN 12:32–12:33</a></p>\n<h3>Concerning the donkey on which he would enter Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:1-Matt21:3\">MAT 21:1–21:3</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:1-Mark11:3\">MRK 11:1–11:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:29-Luke19:31\">LUK 19:29–19:31</a></p>\n<h3>The fall of Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:1-Matt24:2\">MAT 24:1–24:2</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:1-Mark13:2\">MRK 13:1–13:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:5-Luke21:6\">LUK 21:5–21:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:15-Matt24:25\">MAT 24:15–24:25</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:14-Mark13:23\">MRK 13:14–13:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:20-Luke21:24\">LUK 21:20–21:24</a></p>\n<h3>That Judas would betray him</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:21-Matt26:25\">MAT 26:21–26:25</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:18-Mark14:20\">MRK 14:18–14:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:21\">LUK 22:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:21\">JHN 13:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:26\">JHN 13:26</a></p>\n<h3>That Peter would deny him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:34\">MAT 26:34</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:30\">MRK 14:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:34\">LUK 22:34</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:38\">JHN 13:38</a></p>\n<h3>Concerning the nature of Peter's death</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:18-John21:19\">JHN 21:18–21:19</a></p>\n<h2>The ability to interpret dreams and so predict the future</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen40:9-Gen40:13\">GEN 40:9–40:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen40:16-Gen40:19\">GEN 40:16–40:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:28-Gen41:32\">GEN 41:28–41:32</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:45\">DAN 2:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan8:26\">DAN 8:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan10:14\">DAN 10:14</a></p>\n<h2>Predictions were made through OT prophets</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:28\">1SA 15:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam28:16-1Sam28:17\">1SA 28:16–28:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:29-1Kgs11:32\">1KI 11:29–11:32</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:5\">HEB 3:5</a></p>\n<h2>Predictions made through some of the first Christians</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:27-Acts11:28\">ACT 11:27–11:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:10-Acts21:11\">ACT 21:10–21:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:17-Jude1:18\">JUD 1:17–1:18</a></p>\n<h2>False predictions</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer28:8-Jer28:17\">JER 28:8–28:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa47:13-Isa47:15\">ISA 47:13–47:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:16\">ACT 16:16</a></p>\n<h2>The Messiah predicted</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:10-1Pet1:11\">1PE 1:10–1:11</a></strong> <em>Most OT references to the coming of the kingdom of God and his Messiah are not, strictly speaking, predictions but promises made by God in which he expresses his intention to save his people through the Messiah.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:52\">ACT 7:52</a></p>",
